{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb6a9b7d6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"300gg–5"},"text":"§ 300gg–5.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Non-discrimination in health care","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a9b7d7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–5/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Providers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A group health plan and a health insurance issuer offering group or individual health insurance coverage shall not discriminate with respect to participation under the plan or coverage against any health care provider who is acting within the scope of that provider’s license or certification under applicable State law. This section shall not require that a group health plan or health insurance issuer contract with any health care provider willing to abide by the terms and conditions for participation established by the plan or issuer. Nothing in this section shall be construed as preventing a group health plan, a health insurance issuer, or the Secretary from establishing varying reimbursement rates based on quality or performance measures.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a9b7d8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–5/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Individuals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of section 218c ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002451"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002451"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of title 29 (relating to non-discrimination) shall apply with respect to a group health plan or health insurance issuer offering group or individual health insurance coverage."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb6a9b7d9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title XXVII, § 2706, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tI/s1201/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title I, § 1201(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/160"},"text":"124 Stat. 160","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb6a9b7da-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb6a9b7db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb6a9b7dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s218c"},"text":"Section 218c of title 29","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original “section 1558 of the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act”, meaning "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s1558"},"text":"section 1558 of Pub. L. 111–148","children":[],"tail":", and was translated as meaning section 18C of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch676"},"text":"act June 25, 1938, ch. 676","children":[],"tail":", which was added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s1558"},"text":"section 1558 of Pub. L. 111–148","children":[],"tail":", to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb6a9b7dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 300gg–5, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373/tXXVII/s2705"},"text":"act July 1, 1944, ch. 373, title XXVII, § 2705","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/204/tVII/s703/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–204, title VII, § 703(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-26"},"text":"Sept. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2947"},"text":"110 Stat. 2947","children":[],"tail":", and amended, which related to parity in mental health and substance use disorder benefits, was renumbered section 2726 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1944-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1944","children":[],"tail":", and transferred to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–26"},"text":"section 300gg–26 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2706 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1944-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1944","children":[],"tail":", was renumbered section 2727 and is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–27"},"text":"section 300gg–27 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Another prior section 2706 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1944-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1944","children":[],"tail":", was successively renumbered by subsequent acts and transferred, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s238e"},"text":"section 238e of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb6a9b7de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb6a9b7df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective for plan years beginning on or after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2014","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s1255"},"text":"section 1255 of Pub. L. 111–148","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg"},"text":"section 300gg of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb6a9b7e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Implementing Protections Against Provider Discrimination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260/dBB/tI/s108"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–260, div. BB, title I, § 108","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/2859"},"text":"134 Stat. 2859","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/116/260/dBB/tI/s108"},"text":"“Not later than ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2022","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary of Health and Human Services, the Secretary of Labor, and the Secretary of the Treasury shall issue a proposed rule implementing the protections of section 2706(a) of the Public Health Service Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–5/a"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 300gg–5(a)","children":[],"tail":"). The Secretaries shall accept and consider public comments on any proposed rule issued pursuant to this subsection for a period of 60 days after the date of such issuance. Not later than 6 months after the date of the conclusion of the comment period, the Secretaries shall issue a final rule implementing the protections of section 2706(a) of the Public Health Service Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300gg–5/a"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 300gg–5(a)","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
